news.title: Mumbai: East Indians seek extra FSI to house growing families in gaothans
news.para: Clusters of charming cottages and Portuguese-style homes, some dating back to the 19th century, are the last remaining vestiges of Mumbai’s urban gaothans or villages, now surrounded by high-rise structures.

news.title: Nagpur civic body clears a building plan in record four days
news.para: The measure has been taken following the bogus contracts scam which was effected after ‘misusing’ username and password of a few staff members.

news.title: Six town planning schemes in Pune region to see light of day this fiscal
news.para: Of the total six, the work on the Mann Mhalunge town planning scheme has already commenced, said officials.

news.title: Day 2 of charging: Six Supertech twin tower floors fitted with explosives
news.para: Officials in Edifice Engineering, the company tasked with bringing down the two towers, said three additional floors in Ceyane had been partially fitted with explosives.

news.title: Prestige Estates aims to sell properties worth Rs 12,000 crore this fiscal
news.para: Prestige Estates Projects Ltd has a strong presence in South India and the company has made its foray into Mumbai market.

news.title: Amrapali homebuyers oppose court receiver's plan to sell unused FAR
news.para: Hundreds of buyers from different Amrapali projects gathered at a park in Techzone 4 and raised slogans against the proposal.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: First batch of explosives reaches site amid tight security
news.para: More than 3,500 kg of explosives will be filled in around 9,400 holes drilled in the columns and shears of the skeletal structures of the twin towers which will be razed to the ground.

news.title: Supreme Court rules in favour of ARCIL in Tulip Star Hotels bankruptcy case
news.para: The appellate tribunal had accepted the hotel operator’s claim that the ARC filed its case against the company under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC) after the limitation period of three years from the date of declaring the asset as non-performing.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation failed to furnish data on illegal buildings: Audit
news.para: The audit report for 2020-21 prepared by the local fund audit department has noted that the officials could not crosscheck details regarding unauthorized constructions as the corporation did not make it available.

news.title: Residents of 14 villages in Sandur get land records for their property
news.para: ​The residents of the villages of the erstwhile princely state of Sandur have been waiting to get these records, validating their claim to the property, and the fact that this event is taking place on Independence Day makes it more special.

news.title: South City, Urbana & The 42 pay Rs 8.5 crore property tax to Kolkata civic body
news.para: Flat owners at Urbana pay a little over Rs 27,000 per annum while those at South City pay just under Rs 24,000 a year, reveal Kolkata Municipal Corporation data.

news.title: Nagpur: Consumer court asks builder to pay Rs 40,000 for contempt
news.para: Holding Rewati Associates and Infrastructure Limited’s director Suhas More guilty of contempt, a bench comprising president Sanjay Patle and members Smita Chandekar and Avinash Prabhune warned the builder of putting him in jail for three months if he failed to pay the amount to the 65-year-old complainant woman.

news.title: Government properties in Amritsar, Jalandhar to be auctioned
news.para: A spokesperson of the housing and urban development department said the auction list included residential plots, SCOs, shops, booths, and high-value school and group housing societies in the prime areas of Amritsar, Jalandhar, Batala, Gurdaspur, Kapurthala, and Phagwara.

news.title: Ansal Properties & Infrastructure posts Rs 8.98 crore loss in April-June 2022
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 115.22 crore in the first quarter of this fiscal from Rs 96.56 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Shriram Properties posts Rs 10.48 crore profit in April-June quarter
news.para: Total income more than doubled to Rs 145.11 crore in the first quarter of this fiscal, from Rs 60.9 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.
